ader\";N;s:8:\"bodytext\";N;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"imagewidth\";N;s:11:\"imageheight\";N;s:11:\"imageborder\";N;s:11:\"imageorient\";N;s:9:\"imagecols\";N;s:10:\"image_zoom\";N;s:6:\"layout\";N;s:11:\"frame_class\";N;s:18:\"space_before_class\";N;s:17:\"space_after_class\";N;s:12:\"sectionIndex\";N;s:9:\"linkToTop\";N;s:16:\"sys_language_uid\";N;s:6:\"hidden\";N;s:9:\"starttime\";N;s:7:\"endtime\";N;s:8:\"fe_group\";N;s:8:\"editlock\";N;s:10:\"categories\";N;s:14:\"rowDescription\";N;}',0,NULL,'','',NULL,124,0,0,0,NULL,0,'',NULL,0,0,0,0),(1058,120,0,0,0,0,0,1582036570,0,0,1582028331,1582023406,13,0,0,768,'textpic','Skilled Programmers','','','<p>Well if you search at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.quora.com/Are-Indians-really-good-at-computer-programming\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Quora</a>&nbsp;about Indian programmers, it seems they are talented. Sounds good, but how sure is this? How sure that the comments left there were not made by Indian companies that deal with that job?</p>\r\n<p>Well, we did some researches about outsourcing in India, according to&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/2008/02/29/mitra-india-outsourcing-tech-enter-cx_sm_0229outsource.html#43926ac57008\" rel=\"noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Forbes</a>&nbsp;Magazine,&nbsp;&nbsp;it exactly says: “Yet, India, for all its glory, is still the world’s back office. India\'s tech industry is a \"services\" industry.</p>\r\n<p>The Indians don’t do the thinking. The customers do. India executes.”</p>',0,0,0,0,0,0,0,2,0,0,0,'default',0,0,'','',NULL,NULL,0,0,0,'','','',0,'12','',1,0,NULL,0,'','',0,0,0,0,NULL,'',0,'',0,'a:30:{s:5:\"CType\";N;s:6:\"colPos\";N;s:6:\"header\";N;s:13:\"header_layout\";N;s:15:\"header_position\";N;s:4:\"date\";N;s:11:\"header_link\";N;s:9:\"subheader\";N;s:8:\"bodytext\";N;s:5:\"image\";N;s:10:\"imagewidth\";N;s:11:\"imageheight\";N;s:11:\"imageborder\";N;s:11:\"imageorient\";N;s:9:\"imagecols\";N;s:10:\"image_zoom\";N;s:6:\"layout\";N;s:11:\"frame_class\";N;s:18